Package org.ejbca.core.model

Class SecConst

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ejbca.core.model.SecConst
  • public final class SecConst
extends Object
    Constants for users and certificates. Constants for Type of user: Type is constructed as a mask since one user can be of several types. To test a user type: 
     if (((type & USER_ENDUSER) == USER_ENDUSER) && ((type & USER_CAADMIN) == USER_ADMINISTOR) || ...
    ...
    Bit usage: bits 0-7 (1:st byte): user types bits 8-15 (2:nd byte): unused bits 16-23 (3:rd byte): unused bits 24-30 (4:th byte): unused Constants for certificates are simple integer types. Constants for Token Types Token type is constructed of integer constants since only one token type can be generated.
    Version:
    $Id: SecConst.java 27422 2017-12-05 14:05:42Z bastianf $
